main event: A witness observed a bright orange-reddish object traveling toward the north for approximately 20 seconds in Garrett, Indiana on September 15, 1966.
interesting points: The object was compared to a flashlight with a red end,The witness observed the object for about 20 seconds,The witness did not report any sound from the object,There was no definitive evidence presented to conclude that the object was not a conventional aircraft,The report did not contain any photographs.
witness description: two witnesses, one of whom was a 13-year-old male
